	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor 58. In MRR 2.434, and Index, 542, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.419, no. 408, 67 B.C., with the inscription C. Piso L. f. Frugi. Cicero's son-in-law.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5051> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5051" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Assigned to Pontus and Bithynia, he gave up his province in order to aid in the recall of Cicero, his father-in-law (Cic. P. Red. in Sen. 38; P. Red. ad Quir. 7; Sest. 54 and 68; Fam. 14.1.4, 2.2, 3.3, and 4.4; cf. Pis. 12)." .
